The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 11 January is 26,538 (3,071.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 06 January, there were 5,755 new confirmed cases (666.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 30 December, there were 4,879 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 18% (876 extra cases).
